                            <comment id="13414247" author="sebb@apache.org" created="Sat, 14 Jul 2012 01:29:25 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The obvious fix is to only set the restart offset immediately before a file transfer.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;On further reflection, does it make sense to change NET to delay the sending of REST until the next file transfer?&lt;br/&gt;
It seems more natural to me to set the offset immediately before starting the transfer.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;So the only change required is to clarify that setRestartOffset() should only be called immediately before a file transfer.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
